New York  Yankees catcher  Jorge Posada  will retire from Major League Baseball tomorrow,
according to the team.  Posada, 40, whoâ€™s played his entire 17-season major-league
career for the Yankees, will make the announcement at a news
conference at Yankee Stadium, the club said in a news release.
ESPN reported on Jan. 7 that Posada planned to retire this
month.  The 40-year-old Posada has a .273 career batting average
with 275 home runs and 1,065 runs batted in since joining the
Yankees in 1995, helping the franchise win five World Series
titles. Last season Posada batted .235 with 14 homers and 44
RBI.  To contact the reporter on this story:
